 <p><span><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://eastlancstt.org.uk/player/francis-kinsella-301/\">Francis Kinsella</a> </span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td>\r\n  <p><span><a rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://eastlancstt.org.uk/team/hyndburn-ttc-c-24/\">Hyndburn TTC C</a> </span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td>\r\n  <p>167</p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td>\r\n  <p>116</p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td>\r\n  <p>69.46%</p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n<p><i>&nbsp;</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p><i>&nbsp;</i></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Overall league Summary </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With just a\r\nmonth of the season left the likely winners, promoted and to be relegated looks\r\nto be decided in most cases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In the\r\nPremier Division Burnley Boys Club, boasting 3 top 5 merit performers (Dave Kay\r\n1st, Martin Wyatt 2nd, Andrea Harrison 5th)\r\nhave a 29 point lead over 2nd placed East Lancs 1st, and\r\nlook sure to retain the league champions crown first won last year. East Lancs\r\nthough are equally sure of the runners up spot helped by another impressive\r\nseason by 4th merit placed player Liam Bedford. Ramsbottom Exiles\r\nDavid Poytress is 4th in the merits. However the battle to avoid\r\nrelegation in the Premier has become quite changed now that a late season\r\nreturn of Michael Moir alongside Graham Young for Hyndburn TTC â€˜Aâ€™ has lifted\r\nthem out of trouble. Unfortunately it now appears that KSB â€˜Aâ€™ , are now\r\nrelegation favourites alongside The Lions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In Division\r\nOne East Lancs 2nd are set to win and have 3 players in the top 5\r\nmerits (Mark Hanson 3rd , Alan Whittle 4th , Ian Haworth\r\n5th ), and the runners up and other team to be promoted is also very\r\nsure in Brierfield â€˜Aâ€™ who boast the divisions best performing player in Jack\r\nKeogh.&nbsp; Hyndburners&nbsp; Duncan Rigby currently holds the second spot\r\nin the merits. Likely to stay in the relegation zone are bottom placed\r\nBrierfield â€˜Bâ€™ and second from bottom Tackyfire.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Old Masters â€˜Bâ€™\r\nare unassailable now in their chasing for Division two honours, and though\r\nhaving not played enough to feature in the official merits, they do have the\r\nbest player by far in Howard Whewell, who has only dropped one set to the\r\nplucky youngster this last week, Zack Geldard of Hyndburn â€˜B. Old Masters\r\nsuccess is a team effort though and feature two top 5 merit players in Ian\r\n&amp; Albert Pickles (2nd &amp; 3rd respectively)â€™.\r\nWhalley Hawks are also sure of promotion having thrashed Rolling Doals in\r\nrecent weeks, and aided by 4th placed merit player Kieron Cunliffe\r\nwho seems to have found his spark again. The Rollers will miss out again\r\ndespite two of the divisions best players (Neil Hepworth 1st in\r\nmerits &amp; Ian Smith 6th in merits). Slayers at the foot of the\r\ntable and Whalley Kites 3rd from bottom are set on course for the\r\nrelegation positions. KSB â€˜Dâ€™ led by 5th merit placed player Carlton\r\nCooper will lift themselves out of relegation trouble when they catch up with\r\ntheir fixtures.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In Division\r\nThree Doals Marauders are uncatchable and the only unbeaten team left in the\r\nwhole of the league, aided by Roman Mychajlshyn &amp; Dave Greenwood (1st\r\n&amp; 3rd in merits). KSB â€˜Eâ€™ are also looking secure for the second\r\npromotion spot with Bernard Milnes 6th in merits and with son Simon\r\nhaving made massive improvement over the season, not to mention his steady hard\r\nto beat brother Paul (if they can persuade the other brother Craig to return\r\nnext season they may well hold their own in division two). Three youths occupy\r\nthe other top 5 merit positions: Will Cooper of KSB F, Eli Smith of Hyndburn\r\nTTC â€˜Dâ€™, &amp; Frances Kinsella of Hyndburn â€˜Dâ€™, who also whilst playing as\r\nreserve in second recently engineered a great 3:2 win over div 2 merit topper\r\nNeil Hepworth).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For info in\r\nhow to start playing TT contact league development office Harry Rawcliffe on Tel\r\n01254 663451</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Burnley</b><b>\r\nFocus</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>There is just\r\na month of the season left, but In the Premier Division Burnley Boys Club,\r\nboasting 3 top 5 merit performers (Dave Kay 1st, Martin Wyatt 2nd,\r\nAndrea Harrison 5th) look sure to retain the East lancs TT league\r\nchampions crown.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In Division\r\nOne &nbsp;Brierfield â€˜Aâ€™ are almost certainly\r\ngoing to be promoted and take the runners up spot, and also currently boast 1st\r\nplace in the individual player merit table in Jack Keogh. Not doing as well are\r\nBrierfield â€˜Bâ€™ at the bottom of Division One and set for relegation.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Burnley are\r\nrepresented by Adpak Aces in Division Two who have had another steady season\r\nand are placed mid table.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>Division\r\nThree has seen new club Best Centre enter two teams with their â€™bestâ€™ team\r\ndoing pleasing well at the moment in 3rd place and their â€˜young\r\nGunsâ€™ in 6th. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best Centre\r\nis open to new players and beginners to join their club on a Monday night (Contact\r\nDarren Wright for more info on 07736473609)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Rossendale Focus</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>With just 4\r\ngames left the highest placed Rossendale based team is Ramsbottom Town â€˜Aâ€™ in 5th\r\nplace in the premier division and the other Rossendale based premier team is\r\nKSB â€˜Aâ€™ who are now struggling second from bottom and in danger of relegation.\r\nThey have premier standard players but not enough in depth to cover when their\r\nbetter players are not available and thus relying on lower division reserves.\r\nOne more good premier standard player could make a big difference (so if your out\r\nthere in the Valley get in touch!)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In Division\r\nOne KSB â€˜Bâ€™ are in a credible 3rd place &amp; Ramsbottom Town B are\r\nplaying well in 4th place with a game in hand on KSB â€˜Bâ€™. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In Division\r\nTwo Bacup team Rolling Doals have had a bad month and have crashed out of the\r\npromotion race after 3 defeats in a row, and likely to finish 3rd or\r\neven 4th now. KSB â€˜Câ€™ who for half a season also showed promotion\r\naspirations are also well out of it and currently 5th. KSB â€˜Dâ€™ are\r\nsecond to bottom but should get to safety when games are caught up with. Two\r\nValley players feature in the merits, Neil Hepworth of Rolling Doals is 1st\r\nat present and Carlton Cooper of KSB â€˜Dâ€™ is 5th.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>In Division\r\nThree two Rossendale teams look favourites for promotion, the unbeaten Doals\r\nMarauders top the division with Roman Mychajlshyn &nbsp;&amp; Dave Greenwood top of the merits, and\r\nthe family Milnes team KSB â€˜Eâ€™ look safe for the runners up spot. KSB F, are 5th\r\nbut boast 3rd placed merit player Will Cooper and Doals Vikings are\r\n6th. A late registered new Valley player is Lee Barnes, who has\r\nrecently taken up the sport and made a great debut for Doals Marauders this\r\nweek winning two matches. He is one to look out for next season! </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span>For info of\r\nhow to start playing TT in Rossendale contact Ramsbottomâ€™s Bryan Edwards on\r\n01617975082, or Doals (Bacup) Neil Hepworth on 07873834942, or KSB\r\n(Rawtenstall) Trevor Elkington on 07981387755.</span></p>','press',1393695136,'visible',4),(82,'Final press report of season 2013-2014','final-press-report-of-season-2013-2014','<p><b><u><span>East Lancs. Table Tennis League: Final\r\nPress Report 5th May 2014:</span></u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>&nbsp;</u></b><b>From\r\nNeil Hepworth (East Lancs. Table Tennis League Press Officer)</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span